      "id": "bf9e75a51918646669f1918a57e0d3f28dac6b1e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-11-14 20:18:58.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 7: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\n(3 inline comments)\n\nIt would be good to convert more of the code to tabs if the patch needs to be refreshed. Whenever there are patches touching so many lines of code, it may as well also do double duty to convert the tabs so that we don't need to break other patch context twice. \n\nJames, have you verified that the cryptoapi has not changed in newer kernels either?  I'd hate to land this patch and then find out that it needs to be reverted because 3.13 already has changed the API again.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 7
    },
    {
      "id": "33d12673712de92848a4ea46486cd38dc25ec76f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 281,
        "name": "Thomas Stibor",
        "email": "thomas@stibor.net",
        "username": "thomas"
      },
      "date": "2013-11-15 13:04:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 7: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nI downloaded the patch, and configured --with-krb5 --enable-gss flags on a Debian wheezy box, kernel 3.6.11.\nThe patch induces following problems:\n\nlustre/ptlrpc/gss/gss_krb5_mech.c: In function ‘keyblock_init’:\nlustre/ptlrpc/gss/gss_krb5_mech.c:154:13: error: assignment from incompatible pointer type [-Werror]\nlustre/ptlrpc/gss/gss_krb5_mech.c:161:2: error: passing argument 1 of ‘crypto_blkcipher_setkey’ from incompatible pointer type [-Werror]\nIn file included from lustre/ptlrpc/gss/gss_krb5_mech.c:56:0:\n/root/kernel/linux-3.6.11/include/linux/crypto.h:965:19: note: expected ‘struct crypto_blkcipher *’ but argument is of type ‘struct ll_crypto_cipher *’\nlustre/ptlrpc/gss/gss_krb5_mech.c: In function ‘keyblock_free’:\nlustre/ptlrpc/gss/gss_krb5_mech.c:204:3: error: passing argument 1 of ‘crypto_free_blkcipher’ from incompatible pointer type [-Werror]\nIn file included from lustre/ptlrpc/gss/gss_krb5_mech.c:56:0:\n/root/kernel/linux-3.6.11/include/linux/crypto.h:900:20: note: expected ‘struct crypto_blkcipher *’ but argument is of type ‘struct ll_crypto_cipher *’\nlustre/ptlrpc/gss/gss_krb5_mech.c: In function ‘krb5_encrypt’:\nlustre/ptlrpc/gss/gss_krb5_mech.c:549:19: error: assignment from incompatible pointer type [-Werror]\nlustre/ptlrpc/gss/gss_krb5_mech.c:553:2: error: passing argument 1 of ‘crypto_blkcipher_blocksize’ from incompatible pointer type [-Werror]\nIn file included from lustre/ptlrpc/gss/gss_krb5_mech.c:56:0:\n/root/kernel/linux-3.6.11/include/linux/crypto.h:936:28: note: expected ‘struct crypto_blkcipher *’ but argument is of type ‘struct ll_crypto_cipher *’\nlustre/ptlrpc/gss/gss_krb5_mech.c:554:17: error: passing argument 1 of ‘crypto_blkcipher_blocksize’ from incompatible pointer type [-Werror]\nIn file included from lustre/ptlrpc/gss/gss_krb5_mech.c:56:0:\n/root/kernel/linux-3.6.11/include/linux/crypto.h:936:28: note: expected ‘struct crypto_blkcipher *’ but argument is of type ‘struct ll_crypto_cipher *’\nlustre/ptlrpc/gss/gss_krb5_mech.c:559:2: error: passing argument 1 of ‘crypto_blkcipher_ivsize’ from incompatible pointer type [-Werror]\nIn file included from lustre/ptlrpc/gss/gss_krb5_mech.c:56:0:\n/root/kernel/linux-3.6.11/include/linux/crypto.h:931:28: note: expected ‘struct crypto_blkcipher *’ but argument is of type ‘struct ll_crypto_cipher *’\nlustre/ptlrpc/gss/gss_krb5_mech.c:560:3: error: passing argument 1 of ‘crypto_blkcipher_ivsize’ from incompatible pointer type [-Werror]\nIn file included from lustre/ptlrpc/gss/gss_krb5_mech.c:56:0:\n...\n...\n...\n\nNote there are still \"ll_\" in lustre/ptlrpc/gss/gss_krb5.h\n\nAdditionally, the proper types of crypto_cipher have to be fixed, e.g.\n\n struct krb5_keyblock {\n-        rawobj_t                 kb_key;\n-        struct ll_crypto_cipher *kb_tfm;\n+        rawobj_t              kb_key;\n+        struct crypto_blkcipher *kb_tfm;\n };\n\nCheers\n Thomas",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 7
    },
